statemenst usually do not return values by design, but a loop break statement returns something, this breaks a little bit the design. Dont know what the best method to include this is.
Solution: Using a runtime exception to propagate up as long as it reaches the Loop Start statement which compares the loop start identifier and rethrows if the identifier does not match, therefore assuming that the loop to be stopped is higher up in the call environment. now it is important to set boundaries for the break signal exceptions, since it should not propagate through procedure calls. There we catch the break signal exception and through an EvaluationException.
